01:02:07.530 --> 01:02:11.200
&gt;&gt; Just, the journal did
it end when you got back

01:02:11.200 --> 01:02:15.030
or did he continue to write
and was there more beyond

01:02:15.030 --> 01:02:17.050
and how his life
developed after that?

01:02:17.050 --> 01:02:18.350
&gt;&gt; Douglas Taurel:
It pretty much ends,

01:02:18.350 --> 01:02:22.470
it pretty much ends the
way I ended it in the play.

01:02:22.470 --> 01:02:25.860
It's actually so well written
and when you're reading it,

01:02:25.860 --> 01:02:30.630
the problem even with Greeny's
diary and my second show --

01:02:30.630 --> 01:02:31.930
I've dealt with that a lot.

01:02:31.930 --> 01:02:36.430
Soldiers, for the most time
they write in fragments,

01:02:36.430 --> 01:02:38.590
a lot of them, because
they're just trying to get

01:02:38.590 --> 01:02:41.910
through the day, and
Greeny did the same thing.

01:02:41.910 --> 01:02:44.790
He wrote huge chunks where
is just tedious boring stuff

01:02:44.790 --> 01:02:47.510
and fragments, fragments, and
then he would just explode

01:02:47.510 --> 01:02:51.540
into this amazing
eloquent prose.

01:02:51.540 --> 01:02:55.340
But when you're reading his
diary, I mean, it ends like,

01:02:55.340 --> 01:02:59.250
it goes into two sections
as you're reading it,

01:02:59.250 --> 01:03:01.920
he's literally running through
the trenches and then Riley dies

01:03:01.920 --> 01:03:03.970
and the this dies, and
explosion, explosion, explosion

01:03:03.970 --> 01:03:07.510
and then literally it says,
"end of entry", like what?

01:03:07.510 --> 01:03:09.350
What do you mean end of entry?

01:03:09.350 --> 01:03:10.650
And you're flicking through it.

01:03:10.650 --> 01:03:13.260
There's got to be another entry,
and next entry starts off with

01:03:13.260 --> 01:03:16.480
"It's October 22nd I've been
in the hospital for two weeks".

01:03:16.480 --> 01:03:19.040
So, that he was injured
in September 28th,

01:03:19.040 --> 01:03:22.170
so you so he's probably
injured fairly bad

01:03:22.170 --> 01:03:26.710
and he probably was unconscious
is what I imagined, and so then,

01:03:26.710 --> 01:03:28.780
then it goes into the
hospital, hospital goes

01:03:28.780 --> 01:03:32.950
on for a long time, they
actually move them to hospitals.

01:03:32.950 --> 01:03:35.480
But then he comes
home and that's,

01:03:35.480 --> 01:03:38.060
and that's basically
how it ends.

01:03:38.060 --> 01:03:40.650
It actually ends with
him making a phone call

01:03:40.650 --> 01:03:43.880
in the snow calling
Leah: "is today I'm going

01:03:43.880 --> 01:03:45.830
to go make a phone call,
it's pretty cold out there

01:03:45.830 --> 01:03:47.130
but I'm going to go
ahead and brave it,

01:03:47.130 --> 01:03:49.630
I want to hear her voice"
and that's the end of diary

01:03:49.630 --> 01:03:50.930
so it's very cinematic.

01:03:50.930 --> 01:03:52.230
