&gt;&gt; Douglas Taurel: Yes, no and
yes, I mean I talked about this

01:04:17.630 --> 01:04:23.430
with my director, but it really
is and I've become a student

01:04:23.430 --> 01:04:25.580
of War because of my,
my next show, my, my,

01:04:25.580 --> 01:04:26.880
the other show that
I've written.

01:04:26.880 --> 01:04:29.830
So, I've been studying
all the battles a lot,

01:04:29.830 --> 01:04:33.100
and all these brave men and
women have, their commitment

01:04:33.100 --> 01:04:36.680
and sacrifice is something that
we can never really measure

01:04:36.680 --> 01:04:40.300
but when you study
the first World War,

01:04:40.300 --> 01:04:43.330
it really is like a horror show.

01:04:43.330 --> 01:04:44.740
I mean because it's
yes, but you have

01:04:44.740 --> 01:04:46.360
to remember it it's
the beginning

01:04:46.360 --> 01:04:48.890
of the Industrial Age is the
beginning of the machinery.

01:04:48.890 --> 01:04:51.470
It was the first time that we
are using machines to fight

01:04:51.470 --> 01:04:56.440
in war and so, society and human
beings really had not been,

01:04:56.440 --> 01:04:58.670
there's actually moments
in the first World War

01:04:58.670 --> 01:05:01.900
where the French were still
trying to fight on Calvary,

01:05:01.900 --> 01:05:03.980
and they kept getting
gunned down by machine guns

01:05:03.980 --> 01:05:07.030
and they couldn't understand why
their tactics won't be in work

01:05:07.030 --> 01:05:08.860
and this went on, on both sides.

01:05:08.860 --> 01:05:13.030
So, they lost, compared
to what Americans lost

01:05:13.030 --> 01:05:15.930
to what the French and English
lost, is a drop in a bucket,

01:05:15.930 --> 01:05:18.710
they lost like 17 million men.

01:05:18.710 --> 01:05:25.010
I mean, it's on, today anybody
did that it would be a revolt.

01:05:25.010 --> 01:05:29.760
So, I think what's surprising
it's just the pure carnage

01:05:29.760 --> 01:05:32.210
of what the war is and the
way Greeny describes it,

01:05:32.210 --> 01:05:35.120
it describes it like dead
men black and decay faces so,

01:05:35.120 --> 01:05:37.560
when you're reading you just
like it's hard to believe so.

01:05:37.560 --> 01:05:39.510
I'll just leave it at that
not to go too deep into it,

01:05:39.510 --> 01:05:48.290
the gore stuff, but it just
how, how violent that war was.

