01:10:08.020 --> 01:10:09.820
Aye aye sir!

01:10:09.820 --> 01:10:43.330
[ Music ]

01:10:43.330 --> 01:10:48.980
I remember the stand the
country over the [inaudible]

01:10:48.980 --> 01:10:52.920
and all the destruction
of [inaudible].

01:10:52.920 --> 01:10:56.150
I was only 13 or 14 years
old then, and just beginning

01:10:56.150 --> 01:11:00.670
to understand what was
going on in the country.

01:11:00.670 --> 01:11:03.740
My grandfather, he
taught very little to me

01:11:03.740 --> 01:11:05.830
about the French
and Indian wars.

01:11:05.830 --> 01:11:08.910
We lived in a small
fond back in Boston,

01:11:08.910 --> 01:11:11.910
little red house surrounded
by birch people trees.

01:11:11.910 --> 01:11:18.290
When I would ask him what
it was like to fight in war,

01:11:18.290 --> 01:11:23.410
he would answer me with the
steely blue eyes of his,

01:11:23.410 --> 01:11:27.380
almost as if the eyes
itself were speaking to me,

01:11:27.380 --> 01:11:34.750
he would say "son war is
hard, you march, you march,

01:11:34.750 --> 01:11:40.070
and you march some more,
don't ever forget that".

01:11:40.070 --> 01:11:42.540
"But that's great grandfather
that's what I want to do,

01:11:42.540 --> 01:11:44.410
I want to fight,
I want to march,

01:11:44.410 --> 01:11:46.790
I want to experience
the excitement of life,

01:11:46.790 --> 01:11:50.500
I want to be a patriot".

01:11:50.500 --> 01:11:53.370
My grandfather he worked
daily in the fields,

01:11:53.370 --> 01:11:55.560
he developed the taste of
agriculture from his days

01:11:55.560 --> 01:12:01.460
in battle, he loved having
his hands in the earth.

01:12:01.460 --> 01:12:05.300
I sometimes catch him,
working in the field smiling

01:12:05.300 --> 01:12:07.530
as he finally achieved
something,

01:12:07.530 --> 01:12:14.760
he'd get up at 4:00 a.m., and
he wouldn't come in to sundown

01:12:14.760 --> 01:12:23.620
and then he'd just sit by
the fire, he'd just stare.

01:12:23.620 --> 01:12:29.370
He seemed to prefer the silence,

01:12:29.370 --> 01:12:35.720
my mother told me he had led
the great invasion of the canon

01:12:35.720 --> 01:12:38.900
and he had fought many,
many great battles.

01:12:38.900 --> 01:12:52.140
One day after dinner I kneel
down by him and I asked him,

01:12:52.140 --> 01:12:56.320
I said "grandfather
please, tell me what it's

01:12:56.320 --> 01:13:06.800
like to really fight in
war, to experience battle",

01:13:06.800 --> 01:13:10.530
he turned to me with
his blue eyes of his

01:13:10.530 --> 01:13:17.850
and he said "truly splintered.

01:13:17.850 --> 01:13:29.570
They become projectiles, jagged
shards of wood going into faces

01:13:29.570 --> 01:13:38.740
and eyes, the forest it screams,
officers and soldiers roar,

01:13:38.740 --> 01:13:45.690
horses shriek, guns are
blasting everywhere,

01:13:45.690 --> 01:13:52.650
and the ground is covered with
the dead and the air resounds

01:13:52.650 --> 01:13:55.230
with the groans of the dying".

01:13:55.230 --> 01:14:00.100
Well I ignored my grandfather's
advice, and I went ahead,

01:14:00.100 --> 01:14:05.070
enlisted, and engaged
myself for the preservations

01:14:05.070 --> 01:14:06.370
for the liberties of America.

01:14:06.370 --> 01:14:07.670
For I thought that now was
the time for us Americans

01:14:07.670 --> 01:14:08.970
to free ourselves from
the English and set

01:14:08.970 --> 01:14:10.270
up a government of our own.

01:14:10.270 --> 01:14:11.570
On this cold morning, I find
myself far away from home,

01:14:11.570 --> 01:14:12.870
away from my farm and my
grandfather was right,

01:14:12.870 --> 01:14:14.170
war is hard, very, very hard.

01:14:14.170 --> 01:14:15.470
We are here in Valley Forge
in freezing temperatures,

01:14:15.470 --> 01:14:16.770
nearly starved, we have
not eaten in four days

01:14:16.770 --> 01:14:18.070
and as many nights except the
piece of [inaudible] a stick

01:14:18.070 --> 01:14:19.370
of wood, if that
can be called food.

01:14:19.370 --> 01:14:20.670
I miss my farm, and I
specially miss my grandfather.

01:14:20.670 --> 01:14:21.970
And I long for the day to be
back in that farm in Boston,

01:14:21.970 --> 01:14:23.270
for I believe I too,
have developed a taste

01:14:23.270 --> 01:14:25.070
of agriculture pursuits.

01:14:25.070 --> 01:15:30.270
