01:15:30.270 --> 01:15:36.020
Dear Bill, I've come to
this wall again to see

01:15:36.020 --> 01:15:39.670
and touch your name,
and as I do,

01:15:39.670 --> 01:15:43.270
I wonder if anybody here
realizes next to your name,

01:15:43.270 --> 01:15:47.230
in this black wall, is
your mother's heart.

01:15:47.230 --> 01:15:49.110
A heartbroken fifteen years ago

01:15:49.110 --> 01:15:54.050
when you lost your
life in Vietnam.

01:15:54.050 --> 01:15:59.580
As I look at you name
William R. Stocks.

01:15:59.580 --> 01:16:05.320
I think of the times I must
have wondered how scared

01:16:05.320 --> 01:16:06.620
and homesick you must have been

01:16:06.620 --> 01:16:08.970
in that strange country
called Vietnam,

01:16:08.970 --> 01:16:13.880
and how it must have
changed you.

01:16:13.880 --> 01:16:16.620
For you were always such
a happy good-looking kid,

01:16:16.620 --> 01:16:18.680
never sad and never unhappy.

01:16:18.680 --> 01:16:23.230
Until the day I die, I'll always
you how you laughed at me,

01:16:23.230 --> 01:16:25.530
even when I was really
angered before I knew we'd be

01:16:25.530 --> 01:16:27.830
laughing together.

01:16:32.040 --> 01:16:35.190
This past New Year's Day
I finally got my answer.

01:16:37.850 --> 01:16:42.610
I talked on the phone
to a friend

01:16:42.610 --> 01:16:43.910
of yours from Michigan, Jim.

01:16:43.910 --> 01:16:48.730
Jim told me had spent
your last Christmas

01:16:48.730 --> 01:16:52.340
and the last four months
of your life with you.

01:16:52.340 --> 01:16:55.540
Jim told me he was
there when you died.

01:16:55.540 --> 01:16:59.150
He saw how the helicopter
crashed.

01:16:59.150 --> 01:17:00.580
How you were scheduled to fly

01:17:00.580 --> 01:17:01.970
and how your pilot
had been replaced

01:17:01.970 --> 01:17:05.060
by a less experienced
pilot and the cause

01:17:05.060 --> 01:17:08.750
of the crash was unknown,
how were you hit by an enemy,

01:17:08.750 --> 01:17:13.060
or hit an enemy far or you
hit a pole or something.

01:17:13.060 --> 01:17:17.300
He also told me how you men
were like sitting ducks,

01:17:17.300 --> 01:17:19.670
they would send you men out in
the open to draw the enemy out

01:17:19.670 --> 01:17:22.570
and then they send in the planes
in the big guns that take over

01:17:22.570 --> 01:17:24.870
but in the meantime --

01:17:30.350 --> 01:17:34.680
Death came to so many of you.

01:17:34.680 --> 01:17:36.500
He also told me instead of a
yellow streak a lot of them

01:17:36.500 --> 01:17:37.800
and got a mean streak.

01:17:37.800 --> 01:17:44.950
You need to stay that streak
got bigger and meaner,

01:17:44.950 --> 01:17:48.230
everyone except you how you stay
the same happy gold lucky kid

01:17:48.230 --> 01:17:50.420
you are when you got to Vietnam.

01:17:50.420 --> 01:17:53.890
And how you warmed the
friendliness to everyone to you,

01:17:53.890 --> 01:17:56.870
and how your lieutenant
nicknamed you Spanky.

01:17:56.870 --> 01:18:00.880
and soon your entire group's
nickname is Spanky's gang.

01:18:04.330 --> 01:18:10.280
He also told me how, how hard
your death was for everyone.

01:18:10.280 --> 01:18:15.220
How you of all people should not
have been the one to have died.

01:18:15.220 --> 01:18:17.520
How you were their --

01:18:33.410 --> 01:18:34.710
How you were their
moral support.

01:18:34.710 --> 01:18:36.010
I know when I got off the phone

01:18:36.010 --> 01:18:37.310
with Jim he must have
relived that all over again.

01:18:37.310 --> 01:18:38.610
I told him how much I love
them, and I thanked them

01:18:38.610 --> 01:18:40.910
for being your friend.

01:18:42.570 --> 01:18:44.890
How lucky you were to
have him as a friend

01:18:44.890 --> 01:18:50.090
and him to have had you.

01:18:50.090 --> 01:18:55.630
It hurts to write these
letters and to leave them here

01:18:55.630 --> 01:19:05.940
at this wall, but I must face
this pain and put it to rest.

01:19:19.050 --> 01:19:21.350
I'm OK son,

01:19:27.080 --> 01:19:29.380
I'll see you next June.

