02:09:42.150 --> 02:09:45.370
&gt;&gt; How did you come up
with this amazing story?

02:09:45.370 --> 02:09:51.880
&gt;&gt; Douglas Taurel: Now I
get a mic, I didn't get one

02:09:51.880 --> 02:09:58.530
for the show but I, what a day?

02:09:58.530 --> 02:10:01.170
So, I, Long story short is,

02:10:01.170 --> 02:10:03.620
I have incredible
empathy for the veterans.

02:10:03.620 --> 02:10:08.450
So, I started creating letters
about 8 years ago when a lot

02:10:08.450 --> 02:10:12.290
of our men and women were coming
back with severe PTSD and a lot

02:10:12.290 --> 02:10:14.870
of stories were in the
newspaper especially about guys

02:10:14.870 --> 02:10:16.960
who couldn't work
and pay their bills.

02:10:16.960 --> 02:10:20.390
That really seem to
pull on my, my strings.

02:10:20.390 --> 02:10:23.440
So, I wanted as an artist,
I wanted to do something

02:10:23.440 --> 02:10:24.740
to give back, I wanted people

02:10:24.740 --> 02:10:28.870
to really understand what
commitment really meant

02:10:28.870 --> 02:10:32.190
so I started creating
these letters and,

02:10:32.190 --> 02:10:33.630
and I started work shopping.

02:10:33.630 --> 02:10:37.450
It you know up front of friends
and this shows changed a lot

02:10:37.450 --> 02:10:39.790
from when I started
like seven years ago,

02:10:39.790 --> 02:10:44.250
but people kept saying
"you got to keep going,

02:10:44.250 --> 02:10:46.100
I think you're on to something".

02:10:46.100 --> 02:10:50.240
So, long story short I, I
found the director Patrick,

02:10:50.240 --> 02:10:53.250
I don't know he's here and
there is, and I said, "you know,

02:10:53.250 --> 02:10:55.510
I got a bunch of
letters from soldiers,

02:10:55.510 --> 02:10:58.100
you want to work
on this with me?"

02:10:58.100 --> 02:11:00.020
So, I did a monologue for
him and he kind of liked I

02:11:00.020 --> 02:11:02.580
and he said "I think we're on to
something" so we put it together

02:11:02.580 --> 02:11:07.470
and we kind of created
the show and I kind of,

02:11:07.470 --> 02:11:08.960
I finally found the
final structure

02:11:08.960 --> 02:11:12.580
that I wanted and
we performed it.

02:11:12.580 --> 02:11:17.040
And I've been doing it for two
years now and I've been all

02:11:17.040 --> 02:11:18.340
over the country with it.

02:11:18.340 --> 02:11:22.150
Last year was at the Kennedy
Center, September I was

02:11:22.150 --> 02:11:24.640
in Connecticut, Virginia,
Kansas.

02:11:24.640 --> 02:11:26.480
I've been in Texas I've
been all over New York.

02:11:26.480 --> 02:11:29.640
It's going to West Point,
it's going to the Citadel.

02:11:29.640 --> 02:11:35.750
And it just, people keep asking
me to do it and I love to do it

02:11:35.750 --> 02:11:39.530
and I love to share the stories
so, that's kind of, I don't know

02:11:39.530 --> 02:11:40.830
if that answers your question,

02:11:40.830 --> 02:11:48.000
that's kind of how it
became what it is today.

