&gt;&gt; Karen Lloyd: One
more question and then.

02:14:26.470 --> 02:14:28.260
&gt;&gt; Douglas Taurel: Of
Mice and Men first of all.

02:14:28.260 --> 02:14:32.720
&gt;&gt; I was going to ask, there
had been like initiatives,

02:14:32.720 --> 02:14:35.850
anything to get veterans
into theater maybe as a way

02:14:35.850 --> 02:14:39.980
for like therapy for PTSD, have
you thought projects like that?

02:14:39.980 --> 02:14:41.280
&gt;&gt; Douglas Taurel:
Yes, there's tons.

02:14:41.280 --> 02:14:43.870
I mean, the theaters
become a really powerful,

02:14:43.870 --> 02:14:46.800
there's two new forms of
therapy that are starting

02:14:46.800 --> 02:14:51.760
to pop up for veterans.

02:14:51.760 --> 02:14:55.650
Equestrian, equestrian
therapy with horses,

02:14:55.650 --> 02:14:58.160
some really good stuff
with that, and theater.

02:14:58.160 --> 02:15:01.020
So, they're getting, there's
project called The Telling

02:15:01.020 --> 02:15:04.030
Project and I've been
back and forth with them.

02:15:04.030 --> 02:15:06.260
But they do, they do what I do

02:15:06.260 --> 02:15:08.930
but they have the veterans
tell their own stories.

02:15:08.930 --> 02:15:12.320
They act out their own stories,
and it's been really powerful

02:15:12.320 --> 02:15:13.880
for them because it's
allowed them to basic,

02:15:13.880 --> 02:15:17.600
the thing with my show
and what veterans need

02:15:17.600 --> 02:15:21.510
which is really hard, and
I'm creating a web series

02:15:21.510 --> 02:15:23.520
for Thomas Edison Military
Academy based on it.

02:15:23.520 --> 02:15:28.560
But they need to talk and
what happens is when you go

02:15:28.560 --> 02:15:33.170
into the military your kind
of revved up to be a warrior

02:15:33.170 --> 02:15:36.190
and destroy all your
vulnerabilities,

02:15:36.190 --> 02:15:38.020
because your vulnerabilities
don't help you

02:15:38.020 --> 02:15:40.060
as a soldier in battle.

02:15:40.060 --> 02:15:43.790
But when you come back, you
need those vulnerabilities

02:15:43.790 --> 02:15:47.150
as a human being to say,
"I'm hurting right now".

02:15:47.150 --> 02:15:50.630
But they're so conditioned
to not be vulnerable

02:15:50.630 --> 02:15:54.200
that they don't know how to
express themselves anymore,

02:15:54.200 --> 02:15:56.240
and that's when the
problem comes because,

02:15:56.240 --> 02:15:59.320
they carry all this stuff
inside and they start,

02:15:59.320 --> 02:16:00.930
they struggle with it.

02:16:00.930 --> 02:16:05.240
And some more than others,
but the ones that can talk

02:16:05.240 --> 02:16:07.160
about it tend to seem to
really help themselves.

02:16:07.160 --> 02:16:08.750
But therapy, I mean theater

02:16:08.750 --> 02:16:12.110
and horse therapy it's
been some two new versions

02:16:12.110 --> 02:16:13.410
that have been popping up.

02:16:13.410 --> 02:16:18.940
The military is even
looking into the theater

02:16:18.940 --> 02:16:27.210
and I did the show in Kansas
for about 300 Vietnam veterans

02:16:27.210 --> 02:16:30.790
and afterward we, we have some
great stories but they all said,

02:16:30.790 --> 02:16:36.170
"it's so cathartic to hear your
stories because it allows me

02:16:36.170 --> 02:16:39.250
to talk about them and it's the
first time that I've been able

02:16:39.250 --> 02:16:42.620
to express them" so, but yes.

02:16:42.620 --> 02:16:46.200
I mean, just for everybody
to know the only 1%

02:16:46.200 --> 02:16:50.240
of our population serve, and
so we put a tremendous amount

02:16:50.240 --> 02:16:53.070
of demand on those
guys, men and women.

02:16:53.070 --> 02:16:58.510
So, it's just good for
us to remember that 1%

02:16:58.510 --> 02:17:02.300
of our population is
our fighting force so.

